    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>In mathematics, the trace of a moving point in continuous extent, either straight or curved, having length but without breadth or thickness. In geometry, the concept of a line can vary with the definition of geometry; for example in analytic geometry, a line is the set of points on a plane having coordinates that satisfy a given linear equation; in incidence geometry, a line may be an independent object distinct from the set of points which lie on it.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
